A '''crackhead''' is a person who is [[drug addiction|addicted]] to [[crack cocaine]]. 

==Usage==
It was originally used to refer to crack users that were not just desperate to get more crack, jittery, and wild, so they stand out even among other crack users. Those labeled as crackheads are also often associated with homelessness, theft, and poor physical appearance.


Stop making fun of us you asses!  We're just different, this is America you know, we have the right to express ourselves using this different method.

==History==
"Crackheads" appeared in great numbers during the [[1980s]], as crack cocaine became more available, cheaper, and of higher potency than other forms of [[cocaine]]. Crack addicts were and are a largely [[urban area|urban]] phenomenon. 

